<div id="banner">
	<h1>The Last Straw</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p><a href="http://www.freesoftware.fsf.org/straw/">Straw</a> is &#8220;the GNOME 2 desktop news aggregator&#8221; and functions very much like <a href="http://ranchero.com/software/netnewswire/">NetNewsWire</a>. It uses some of Mark Pilgrim&#8217;s great little RSS tools (rssparser, rssfinder, etc.) and BerkeleyDB for storage. Linux, Python, GPL. Nice!</p>

<p>I love apps like this that take all the pieces lying around and glue them together.</p>

<p class="posted">posted September 13, 2002 12:53 AM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_technology">Technology</a>)  <a href="000591" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

